# DELIVERY.md

## How to run

This workflow seeds starter bounty issues and ensures each issue body includes a parent bounty reference to the canonical Bug Bounty Program issue (if found).

1. Push this workflow to your repo.
2. Go to GitHub Actions > Seed Starter Bounty Issues > Run workflow.
3. Enter comma-separated issue titles and bodies.

Each seeded issue will include `Parent bounty: #<number>` at the top of the body if the canonical issue exists.

## Example
- Issue titles: `Bug: Widget fails on load, Bug: API returns 500`
- Issue bodies: `Acceptance: Widget loads, /bounty $50, Acceptance: API returns 200, /bounty $50`

## Requirements
- The canonical issue must be titled exactly `Bug Bounty Program — How to Participate` and not be a PR.
